before.enText: of a group of similar things

data.enText: to be different from each other in size, shape, etc.

data.chText: 学生作业的质量甚是参差不齐。
data.enText: The students' work varies considerably in quality.

data.chText: 学生作业的质量甚是参差不齐。
data.enText: The quality of the students' work varies considerably.

data.chText: 引进新技术的成功程度不尽相同。
data.enText: New techniques were introduced with varying degrees of success.
to change or be different according to the situation
The menu varies with the season.

data.chText: 价格随所要求的户型而有所变化。
data.enText: Prices vary according to the type of room you require.
‘What time do you start work?’ ‘ It varies .’
to make changes to sth to make it slightly different

data.chText: 这项工作使我能够调整工作时间。
data.enText: The job enables me to vary the hours I work.

ex.chText: 女巫把那男孩变成了一只老鼠。
ex.enText: A witch changed the boy into a mouse.

ex.chText: 经济形势已发生了相当大的变化。
ex.enText: The economic situation has changed considerably.
The leaves on the trees change colour in the autumn.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指任何变化，强调与原先的情况有明显的不同。

ex.chText: 你的外衣太大了，得找人改一下。
ex.enText: Your coat is too big. You must have it altered.

ex.chText: 工作环境必须改善，以适应新的要求。
ex.enText: The working condition must be altered to meet the new requirements.

synonyms.bx: 常指轻微改变，强调在保持原状的情况下进行局部改变。

ex.chText: 请把这钱兑换成人民币。
ex.enText: Please convert this money into RMB.
Her mother has converted to Catholicism.

synonyms.bx: 指改变形式、用途、使用方式等，也指改变信仰、观点、态度等。

ex.chText: 这项计划要用就必须修改。
ex.enText: The plan must be modified if it is to be used.

ex.chText: 你最好说得和缓些才是。

synonyms.bx: 指对某物作细小的改动以对其进行改进，使其更适用或更高效。

ex.chText: 魔术师把那条手帕变成了一只鸟。
ex.enText: The magician transformed the handkerchief into a bird.

ex.chText: 太阳能可以转化为能量。
ex.enText: Solar energy can be transformed into power.

synonyms.bx: 指在形式、外观、性质等方面彻底改变，即成为全新的东西。

ex.enText: Coal can be turned into heat.

ex.chText: 他把这本小说变成了英语畅销书。
ex.enText: He turned this novel into an English best-seller.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指外形、颜色、气味、性质等方面发生变化。

ex.chText: 鱼的价格随着市场行情而变化。
ex.enText: The prices of fish vary according to market conditions.

ex.chText: 老年人不喜欢改变他们的习惯。
ex.enText: Old people don't like to vary their habits.

synonyms.bx: 指根据某一情况的变化而变化，也指更改某事物。

tr: become different in some particular way, without permanently losing one's or its former characteristics or essence
example: her mood changes in accordance with the weather
The supermarket's selection of vegetables varies according to the season

tr: make something more diverse and varied
be subject to change in accordance with a variable
example: His moods vary depending on the weather

value.def: If things vary, they are different from each other in size, amount, or degree.

example.ex: As they're handmade, each one varies slightly...
example.tran: 由于它们是手工制作的，彼此都会有些微小的差异。

example.ex: The text varies from the earlier versions...
example.tran: 这一文本与较早的版本有些不同。

example.ex: Different writers will prepare to varying degrees.
example.tran: 不同作者的准备程度也会各不相同。

value.def: If something varies or if you vary it, it becomes different or changed.

example.ex: The cost of the alcohol duty varies according to the amount of wine in the bottle...
example.tran: 酒税税额随酒瓶容量的大小而有所不同。

example.ex: You are welcome to vary the diet.
example.tran: 我们鼓励不时变换饮食。

trans: 随……变化；而变化；随…而变化
在……方面变化；在……方面有差异
